headline: Medtronic lifts annual profit view on strong demand for medical devices
summary: The Ireland-based company expects profit in the range of $5.44 to $5.50 per share for fiscal year 2025, compared with its earlier forecast of $5.42 to $5.50.  Investors had set a high bar for results from medical device makers as the companies continue to benefit from healthy demand for non-urgent surgeries, especially among older Americans, over the last few quarters.  Peers Boston Scientific and Abbott had also raised their annual profit forecasts last month.
